    Infographic Narrative & Structure Plan:
    1. Introduction/Hook: "Beyond Monitoring, Towards Proactive Intelligence." - Establish the core value proposition.
    2. Core Technology: "The 'Brain' - High-Performance Edge AI." - Showcase the RK3588's power to build technical credibility.
    3. On-Device AI: "The 'Intelligence' - Privacy-First AI Models." - Explain the key differentiator of on-device processing.
    4. Data Fusion: "The 'Senses' - A Holistic View of Health." - Visualize the multi-modal data collection process.
    5. User Insights: "The 'Insight' - From Data to Action." - Demonstrate the user-facing metrics and trend analysis.
    6. Security Architecture: "The 'Fortress' - A Commitment to Privacy." - Illustrate the multi-layered security model to build trust.
    7. Extensibility: "The 'Future' - A Platform Built to Evolve." - Show the modular design and future potential for investors.
    -->

    <!-- 
    Visualization Selection & Justification:
    - Section 1 (Intro): Single Big Number/Statement. Goal: Inform. Justification: Grabs attention. Method: HTML/CSS.
    - Section 2 (Core Tech): Horizontal Bar Chart. Goal: Compare. Justification: Clearest way to compare specs of RK3588 vs competitors. Library: Chart.js.
    - Section 3 (On-Device AI): Bubble Chart. Goal: Compare. Justification: Shows multiple dimensions (model size, privacy, latency) effectively. Library: Chart.js.
    - Section 4 (Data Fusion): Flow Chart. Goal: Organize. Justification: Best way to represent a process flow. Method: HTML/CSS (No SVG/Mermaid).
    - Section 5 (User Insights): Donut Chart & Line Chart. Goal: Compare (Composition) & Change (Time). Justification: Donut for parts-of-a-whole, Line for time-series data. Library: Chart.js.
    - Section 6 (Security): Layered Diagram. Goal: Organize. Justification: Visually represents layered defense. Method: HTML/CSS (No SVG).
    - Section 7 (Extensibility): Block Diagram. Goal: Organize. Justification: Clear way to show modular components. Method: HTML/CSS (No SVG).

    All visualizations adhere to the NO SVG and NO MERMAID JS constraints.
    -->
    
